:"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William De Bracci was born in 1340, in England, United Kingdom. He married De Braccu before 1383, in Seal, Kent, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1390, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1340–1390":"1340–1390","1365–1405":"1365–1405","1383–1439":"1383–1439","1365":"1365","before 1383":"enne 1383","1340":"1340","1383":"1383","1390":"1390","1439":"1439","1405":"1405","Seal, Kent, England":"Seal, Kent, England","Seal, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Seal, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1340–1390":"1340–1390","1365–1405":"1365–1405","1383–1439":"1383–1439","1365":"1365","before 1383":"ennen vuotta 1383","1340":"1340","1383":"1383","1390":"1390","1439":"1439","1405":"1405","Seal, Kent, England":"Seal, Kent, England","Seal, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Seal, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1340–1390":"1340–1390","1365–1405":"1365–1405","1383–1439":"1383–1439","1365":"1365","before 1383":"avant 1383","1340":"1340","1383":"1383","1390":"1390","1439":"1439","1405":"1405","Seal, Kent, England":"Seal, Kent, Angleterre","Seal, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Seal, Kent, Angleterre,